    "Particularly, at D 1 = 22000, the PCC value increases to 0.8440, surpassing the previous value of 0.8436, and the MSE decreases to 0.0238, lower than the previous value of 0.0240.When y i > σ 1, f i (x) > 0 and f i (x) > 0, as σ 1 increases in intervals of 0.05, the Pcc first increases sharply, then slowly increases to 0.8407, then slowly decreases, and finally decreases sharply; MSE first decreases sharply, then slowly decreases to 0.0231, then slowly increases, and finally increases sharply, as listed in the middle part of Table 4.The main reason is as follows.",
    "If D 1 is set as a constant, the calculated sentence similarity x i is unchangeable.",
    "For each sentence pair, if the three parameters x i, y i and λ 1 are fixed values, f i (x) and g i (x) are also fixed values, as shown in Eqs. 16 and 17.",
    "Consequently, whether sentence pairs need to be recalculated by SQE is only determined by σ 1.",
    "When σ 1 is large, with the increase of σ 1, the threshold of annotated sentence similarity y i that satisfies the recalculation conditions increases, so that the number of the sentence pairs to be recalculated decreases."
